143	<div class="wrap">
144	  <div class="container">
145	
146	    <!-- 1 · HERO -->
147	    <header class="hero">
148	      <p class="kicker">Analysis &middot; Deep Research Benchmark</p>
149	      <h1>It outscores the frontier labs at deep research &mdash; and runs on open weights you host yourself.</h1>
150	      <p class="lede">A deep&#8209;research system plans a question, searches the live web, and writes a report in which every claim is cited. Measured by RACE, the field&rsquo;s standard quality score, Deep Cove Research places third among the systems tested here &mdash; ahead of the closed models from Google, OpenAI, Anthropic and xAI. It is the highest&#8209;scoring system a company can run on its own hardware.</p>
151	
152	      <div class="stats">
153	        <div class="stat">
154	          <div class="num pos">0.5084</div>
155	          <div class="lab">Composite quality (RACE)</div>
156	          <div class="sub">3rd overall &middot; 1st among open weights</div>
157	        </div>
158	        <div class="stat">
159	          <div class="num pos">90.3%</div>
160	          <div class="lab">Citation accuracy</div>
161	          <div class="sub">claims that held up against live sources</div>
162	        </div>
163	        <div class="stat">
164	          <div class="num pos">84</div>
165	          <div class="lab">Verified citations</div>
166	          <div class="sub">the most of any system we measured</div>
167	        </div>
168	      </div>
169	      <p class="byline">Scored on DeepResearch&nbsp;Bench under the RACE framework. Rows marked &dagger; below are the official 100&#8209;task leaderboard; the rest are our own runs of each system&rsquo;s latest model on one shared task.</p>
170	    </header>
171	
172	    <!-- 2 · WHAT IT IS -->
173	    <section>
174	      <p class="eyebrow">What it is</p>
175	      <h2>An autonomous analyst, not a chatbot answer.</h2>
176	      <p class="narrow">Ask a deep&#8209;research system an open&#8209;ended question and it does what a research analyst would. It breaks the question into parts, searches many sources, reads and extracts the evidence, weighs which sources to trust, reconciles the ones that disagree, and writes a long, structured report in which every claim carries a citation. The answer does not come from a model&rsquo;s memory. It is assembled &mdash; search, verification, and synthesis, run end to end with no human in the loop.</p>
177	    </section>
178	
