281	      </div>
282	      <p class="cap">Deep Cove Research ranks third overall and first among systems a company can run itself. Only ADORE, an academic submission, and Tavily, a closed commercial framework, score higher. <span class="dag">&dagger;</span>&nbsp;Official DeepResearch&nbsp;Bench leaderboard, 100&#8209;task average. Unmarked rows are our own runs of each system&rsquo;s latest model on the shared benchmark task, scored on the same GPT&#8209;5.5 harness; a full 100&#8209;task submission for Deep Cove Research is in progress.</p>
283	    </section>
284	
285	    <!-- 4 · FAITHFULNESS CHART -->
286	    <section>
287	      <p class="eyebrow">Faithfulness</p>
288	      <h2>Accuracy and volume rarely travel together.</h2>
289	      <p class="narrow">A citation can fail two ways: the source may not support the claim, or the report may rest on too few citations to stand on. Most systems managed one and not the other. Deep Cove Research sits alone in the top&#8209;right corner &mdash; high accuracy on a wide base of sources.</p>
