335	    </section>
336	
337	    <!-- 5 · TWO APPROACHES -->
338	    <section>
339	      <p class="eyebrow">Two ways to build one</p>
340	      <h2>Curated dataset, or the open internet.</h2>
341	      <p class="narrow">There are two ways to build a deep&#8209;research system, and they solve different problems. One reads from a dataset that has already been collected, cleaned, and frozen. The other reads the live internet as it is &mdash; messy, contradictory, unbounded &mdash; and must find, judge, and verify the evidence itself on every run. The first is a useful tool. The second is a general research engine, and it is the one the frontier labs are racing to build.</p>
342	      <div class="card" style="overflow-x:auto">
343	        <table>
344	          <thead>
345	            <tr><th></th><th class="mute">Curated&#8209;dataset system</th><th>Open&#8209;internet system</th></tr>
346	          </thead>
347	          <tbody>
348	            <tr><td>Evidence</td><td class="mute">A fixed corpus you pre&#8209;assemble and clean</td><td><span class="g">The entire live web, in real time</span></td></tr>
349	            <tr><td>Coverage</td><td class="mute">Only what was curated &mdash; blind to the rest</td><td><span class="g">Any topic, any domain, including today</span></td></tr>
350	            <tr><td>Freshness</td><td class="mute">Frozen &mdash; stale the moment it is built</td><td><span class="g">Always current</span></td></tr>
351	            <tr><td>The hard part</td><td class="mute">Assembling the corpus once</td><td><span class="g">Search, credibility, dedup &amp; verification &mdash; solved live, every run</span></td></tr>
352	            <tr><td>Generalizes?</td><td class="mute">No &mdash; one dataset, one domain</td><td><span class="g">Yes &mdash; one engine for every question</span></td></tr>
353	            <tr><td>Who builds it</td><td class="mute">Teams not yet able to handle the open web</td><td><span class="g">OpenAI, Google, Anthropic &mdash; and Deep Cove Research</span></td></tr>
354	          </tbody>
355	        </table>
356	      </div>
357	      <p class="cap">A curated&#8209;dataset system is a <strong>special case</strong> of an open&#8209;internet one. A general engine can always be pointed at a fixed corpus; a curated system cannot be opened to the live web without first solving the harder problem. That is why the open&#8209;internet path is the foundational one &mdash; and it is the one Deep Cove Research is built on.</p>
358	    </section>
